Problem 7.6:

ZipGeography = (ZipGeography)
ZipGeography %>%
 filter(!(Timezone %in% " ") | is.na(Timezone)) %>%
 ggplot() +
 aes(x = Population, y = LandArea) +
 geom_point(size = 1L, colour = "#0c4c8a") +
 theme_minimal() +
 facet_wrap(vars(State))
## Warning: Removed 10572 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

new_ZipGeography <-
  ZipGeography %>%
  group_by(State) %>%
  summarise(sum_population = sum(Population, na.rm = TRUE) )
mUSMap(new_ZipGeography, key = "State", fill = "sum_population")
## Mapping API still under development and may change in future releases.
## Warning in standardName(x, stateAlternatives, ignore.case = ignore.case, : 2
## items were not translated

noval_ZipGeography <-
  ZipGeography %>%
  group_by(State) %>%
  summarise(unit_area_state = (sum(LandArea, na.rm = TRUE) /sum(Population, na.rm = TRUE)) )
mUSMap(noval_ZipGeography, key = "State", fill = "unit_area_state")
## Mapping API still under development and may change in future releases.
## Warning in standardName(x, stateAlternatives, ignore.case = ignore.case, : 2
